history.content:
Hey everyone! I wanted to share this event that I think a lot of you would be interested in:

Between working as an engineer, product manager, and founder of 2 internal startups at Google (one of which was acquired by the company), Neel Rao (class of 2014) has built and launched diverse products across a number of verticals.

Join us on Friday at 4pm PT as Neel discusses his learnings from these experiences. From joining Google’s APM program, to selling his Area 120 VR/AR team to Google, to finally launching GameSnacks (his current Area 120 team), Neel’s talk will cover insights that should be valuable to many.

Register Here: https://zoom.us/meeting/register/tJ0ucuygrj8uEtF2eQA0aFSMKOAJDKkrzx79

This talk is part of Florian's weekly event series. Florian is a community of Cal alumni helping students pay for school without loans and get ahead in their careers; you can learn more at joinflorian.com.
